HSF Awarded Bunnahabhain Humanitarian Award The Helen Suzman Foundation is pleased to announce that it was nominated and subsequently awarded The Bunnahabhain Humanitarian Award in honour of Chief Rabbi Harris by the South African Jewish Report and ABSA. The Award is shared with Freedom Under Law (“FUL”). Previous recipients of this award include Pravin Gordhan, Advocate Thuli Madonsela and Advocate George Bizos. The award recognises the HSF and FUL’s contribution to defending our constitutional democracy. We were especially delighted to receive the award from Anne Harris, the widow of Rabbi Harris, at a gala dinner in Johannesburg on Sunday 2 September 2018. Issued by Helen Suzman Foundation, 3 September 2018